.TH GIT-WORKTREE-AUDIT 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-worktree-audit \- report state across all worktrees
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git worktree-audit
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git worktree-audit
lists every worktree with its path, checked-out branch, dirty state, last commit
age, and the open pull request number when GitHub data is available.
.PP
A worktree whose directory no longer exists is reported as an orphan. Dirty
state is reported as
.B unknown
for bare or orphaned worktrees, which have no working tree to inspect. PR lookup
is best-effort: when
.B gh
is missing or unauthenticated the audit still reports local worktree state and
omits PR numbers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print stable tab-separated
.B worktree
records:
.BR path ,
.B branch
(or
.B detached
or
.BR bare ),
.B dirty
(true/false/unknown),
.B orphan
(true/false),
.B pr
number (may be empty),
.B HEAD
commit, and
.B committerdate
as a Unix timestamp.
.TP
.B \-\-prune-orphan
Prune worktrees whose directory no longer exists, delegating to
.BR "git worktree prune" .
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry-run
With
.BR \-\-prune-orphan ,
print what would be pruned without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Audit or prune completed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-worktree (1),
.BR git-branch-audit (1),
.BR git-repo-state (1)
